      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:50:6",
      "text": [
        " مَنْ حَمَلَ السِّلَاحَ بِاللَّيْلِ فَهُوَ مُحَارِبٌ إِلَّا أَنْ يَكُونَ رَجُلًا لَيْسَ مِنْ أَهْلِ الرِّيبَةِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Al Hassan Bin Mahboub, from Ali Bin Raib, from Zureys Al Kunasy, ",
          "Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘The one who carries the weapon at night, so he is a combatant, except if he happens to be a man who is not from the doubtful people’."
        ]
      }
